    ('SOC-S 110', 'CHARTS, GRAPHS, AND TABLES', '12237', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'BH 008', 'Eehyun Kim', 4, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GLOBAL & INTERNATIONAL STUDIES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Develops students'' skills as consumers and producers of charts, graphs, and tables. Students learn to use data to depict social trends; assess political programs; and test social science theories. Students learn how to find, read, interpret, and evaluate graphical information, and how to present results in engaging formats.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd N&M credit
